Bhandara is 65 KM away from Nagpur on Nagpur ‚ÄìRaipur highway. It is situated on the bank of Vainganga River.

text.text: The temple of Maa Ambai Nimbai Mata is located in Bhandara city, 60 km from Nagpur. This temple is about 1000 years old and the idol of Mata Ji is about 800 years old. The idols of Mata Ji are made in Hemadpanthi style and came into existence during the rule of Gond dynasty. According to the old saying, about 800 years ago, there were two trees, one of mango and one of neem, due to a strong storm both the trees fell, after that two statues appeared from between the two trees which were known as Maa Ambai and Nimbai. . Ambai is the form of mango tree and Nimbai is the form of Neem tree. Jai Mata Di.
The wait of years was completed with the darshan of Mata Ji.
